
Git is an open source distributed version control system (VCS)
VCS is the ultimate time travel machine for a project
Git is a tool that tracks changes to source code

Each commit is a different version of the project

Version control systems like git is NOT a backup, it is just a repository of different versions of a project.

Version control is useful to:
·         track a projects's history
·         manage multiple versions of a project
·         share code amongst developers
·         coordinate teamwork

Git's strong points --- fast, safe, flexible, smart

Git's shortcomings: Not ideal for binary files and not user-friendly

Git is hard to learn, but easy to use

Versiyon kontrol sistemleri olmasa farklı modülleri biraraya getirmede çok sıkıntı yaşanırdı.
Database, user, administrator interface ve farklı developer kodlarının bulunduğu modulleri bir araya getirmede entegrasyon problemi yaşanırdı.

